<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-18-0476 </DOCNO><TEXT>The computer-aided design of complex electron-optical systems proceedsin several stages, including field calculation, aberration evaluationand exploration of the effects of parasitic aberrations caused by misalignment,for example. We recall that the geometry and excitation of each componentof a complex sequence can be dissociated from the magnifications at whichthe component is operating and we show how this useful separation canbe achieved for superimposed deflection and round lens fields.</TEXT></DOC>